"a.可耻的；耻辱的 【英】 adj. 可耻的(contemptible ; despicable)；耻辱的(shameful) 【考】 反义词：lofty(崇高 的); honorable(可敬的) adj. 可耻的(不名誉的) = contemptible = despicable; 堕落卑鄙的 【反】lofty(adj 高高的; 崇高的); honorable(adj 可敬的; 光荣的) 【记】ig 否定 + nomi 名 (name 名字) 不好的名声，使丢掉名气，使有名的人蒙羞 【相关】nominate 提名 ignominious (adj.)  early 15c., from Middle French ignominieux (14c.) or directly from Latin ignominiosus ""disgraceful, shameful,"" from ignominia ""loss of a (good) name,"" from assimilated form of in- ""not, opposite of"" (see in- (1)) + nomen (genitive nominis) ""name"" (see name). Influenced by Old Latin gnoscere ""come to know."" Related: Ignominiously; ignominiousness."
